xl200.DisableSortingItems.help: Allow changing the items sequence inside an order.
alertAgentOfflineDesc: The Agent service cannot be contacted.
xl200.EnforceEclipseCoilValidation.help: When this parameter is set to YES, the machine will not be allowed to enter the run mode after a new coil is loaded until the coil is validated by Eclipse. Eclipse Coil Validation can be disabled by turning off the setup lockout key.
availabilityPctHelp:
Simple definition: the percentage of scheduled production time the machine is actually running. Note: using time-based percentage only works when the range of products being produced all have the same target production speed. When calculating an aggregate value across a range of mixed product target speeds, it is necessary to use ratios of production values (length, weight, etc).

Calculation: sum(Running Time * Rated Speed) / sum( Available Time * Rated Speed) ) where Available Time = total time - exempt time
runPctHelp:
Ratio of time the machine was in run to the total time, including unscheduled time.

Calculation: Run Minutes/Total Minutes
xl200.AutoRequestOrder.help: When the controller's remaining total footage drops below this value, it will automatically send a request for ECLIPSE to download more orders to run.
oEEHelp:
OEE = Overall Equipment Effectiveness
This is the ratio of actual good production to the theoretical output if the machine ran 100% of the scheduled (available) production time at 100% of the rated speed for the current product and 100% yield (no bad parts).

Calculation: sum(Good product) / sum( Available Time * Rated Speed) ) where Available Time = total time - exempt time
reclaimedScrapFeetHelp: The amount of material that was previously reported as scrap that was reclaimed as good. This value is also included in the Total Good value.
xl200.EnforceBundlingRules.help: When set to Yes, certain rules like forcing Dec Qty to be within the current Order and Bundle will be enforced to ensure reporting and bundling accuracy.
redirectToIntranetUrlDescription: When localhost is detected, automatically redirect the browser to
xl200.ShearScrapLength.help: Defines the maximum length of material that can be manually cut without prompting the operator to record a scrap code. This feature is only active if the controller is connected to ECLIPSE. It can be disabled by entering a value of 999".
xl200.AutoDeleteDoneOrdersAfter.help: Defines the number of days before a DONE order is automatically deleted. Completed orders are tested at noon and midnight each day to see it enough time has expired for them to be deleted.
alertCommOfflineDesc: No data has been received from Eclipse-Comm in a long time.
eclipseServerURLIsNotCorrect: Eclipse Server URL is not correct
xl200.UseCoilInventory.help: Enables or disables the use of the controller's Coil Inventory.
speedPctHelp:
The ratio of actual running speed to the target production speed for the product. The target production speed is defined based on the equipment's capabilities for the current product and length. When calculating an aggregate value across a range of mixed product target speeds, it is necessary to use ratios of production values (length, weight, etc).

Calculation: sum(Good & Bad Quantity * Part Length) / sum( Available Time * Rated Speed) ) where Available Time = total time - exempt time
AdministratorRequiredToAllowGuestUser: Administrator role required to allow guest user
xl200.SetDoneItemsToReady.help: If NO is selected when an item is run to completion, it takes a status of DONE and can not be run again. If YES is selected, items become READY after they have been run to completion. This allows the same item to be run over and over again without reprogramming it. Note that running with YES selected may cause unexpected footage totals and erroneous ECLIPSE reports.
scrapFeetHelp:
Amount of material consumed that did not end up as a good part. This includes bad parts as well as scrap caused by manual shears, coil thread-up & tail-out, etc.

Note: for some products the length of material consumed does not equal the finished part length. In those cases the total good length plus total net scrap will not add up to match the total length consumed.

Calculation: sum(material consumed) - sum(number of good parts * expected material consumed/part)
targetPctHelp:
Ratio of actual good production to the theoretical output if the machine ran according to established standards.

100% Target means all coil, material, tooling changeovers take the time given by the standard work definition for a safe change & besides changeovers, 100% of the scheduled production time is spent running, the machine runs at 100% of the rated speed for the current product, 100% of the parts produced are good.

Calculation: sum(Good product) / sum( (Available - Standard Changeover time) * Rated Speed) ) where Available Time = total time - exempt time
xl200.HaltDelayMinimum.help: Defines the length of time the machine may be halted without requiring a Halt Delay Reason. If the machine sits idle for a length of time longer than the Halt Delay Minimum, the operator will be prompted to enter his Employee ID and a Delay Reason upon re-initiating the run mode. This feature may be disabled by entering a value of 99 minutes.
xl200.AllowCoilOverride.help: Determines whether the machine operator is allowed to run an order whose material code doesn't match the material code of the current coil. Selecting ONLY WITH KEY requires the Setup Lockout key to perform the coil override.
scrapPctHelp:
The ratio of scrap material to the total material consumed.

Calculation: sum(Scrap Length) / sum(Total Length Consumed)
xl200.UseScrapCodes.help: Enabling Scrap Codes causes the controller to prompt the operator to enter a code whenever scrap material is produced (i.e. Manual Shear, Increment Quantity, etc.). The code will be reported to ECLIPSE to provide accurate data for material usage reports.
xl200.DisplayBundleIdPrompts.help: When Set to YES a prompt showing the Bundle ID and other identifying information about the Bundle will be displayed when a bundle completion event occurs.
yieldPctHelp:
The percentage of parts parts that were good.  Note: good parts includes parts that were reworked from bad parts or reclaimed from scrap material.

Calculation: sum(Good product) / sum(Good & Bad Quantity * Part Length)
throughputHelp:
Average production rate when the machine is running.

Calculation: sum(Good product) / sum(Run minutes)
alertAgentConfigurationDesc: The Agent service is not configured correctly.
showMaterialShortageAlertsDescription: If Eclipse does not contain the full coil inventory all orders will have alerts. SQL Coil Validation does not store the coil inventory in Eclipse.
goodFeetHelp:
Total amount of good production by finished length or weight as well as the total number of good parts. These totals include parts that were originally good as well as those reclaimed from previously reported scrap.

Calculation: sum(number of good parts * finished part length)
